["Rules#6: Avoid hardcoding credentials directly in code. Use environment variables, configuration files with appropriate access controls, or secure vaults to manage credentials securely."],
["Rules#7: Ensure the use of strong, industry-standard encryption algorithms and key lengths appropriate for the sensitivity of the data. Use AES-256-GCM for symmetric encryption with a 128-bit tag. Specify the mode and padding explicitly. In Java use AES/GCM/NoPadding with GCMParameterSpec(128, iv). Key derivation: Derive encryption keys from passphrases with PBKDF2-HMAC-SHA-256, a unique 16-byte salt per file, and at least 210,000 iterations. Store the salt with the ciphertext. Prefer scrypt or Argon2id if available.

