["Rules#8: To mitigate CWE-759, always use a unique salt when hashing sensitive data such as passwords, Make always salt unpredictable, don't use static value even for testing. This prevents attackers from easily comparing hashes using rainbow tables or other precomputed hash attacks."],
["Rules#9: Use a strong, cryptographically secure random number generator to create salts that are unpredictable and unique for each input, such as a password."],
["Rules#10: Always incorporate OAEP when using the RSA algorithm to ensure optimal encryption security."],
