["Rules#8: Always use vetted cryptographic libraries and modern algorithms. Never implement cryptography or TLS logic manually. Ban MD5, SHA-1, DES/3DES, RC4, and ECB mode. Use AEAD encryption such as AES-GCM or ChaCha20-Poly1305. Derive keys with Argon2id, scrypt, or PBKDF2-HMAC-SHA-256 and a random salt. Use a secure random generator for all keys, salts, and nonces. Use RSA with OAEP (\u22652048 bits) or modern curves like X25519 and Ed25519. Enforce TLS 1.2 or TLS 1.3 and never disable certificate validation.

